# NeuroCode — Agentic VS Code Extension
# Cursor Rules File v2.0 — AI Constitution for this Project
# Author: ZMS Digital Solutions — Dhaka, Bangladesh
# Stack: TypeScript + Node.js Sidecar + React WebView + Ollama/vLLM
# Acquisition Target: Google / Meta / SpaceX / GitHub

## PROJECT IDENTITY

You are building **NeuroCode** — a VS Code extension that enables agentic coding on low-end GPUs
by intelligently splitting codebases into small context shards and routing them through local or
remote LLMs. This is NOT a wrapper around Copilot. It is a ground-up agentic system built for
acquisition — every architectural decision must create a defensible moat.

Three moats being built simultaneously:
1. **The Shard Architecture** — runs agentic coding on 4GB VRAM (technical moat)
2. **The Edit Genome** — opt-in dataset of human-verified code edits (data moat)
3. **Air-Gap Mode** — the only agentic coder that works in classified/regulated environments (market moat)

---

## FULL ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW

The system has 3 main processes plus 2 background subsystems:

```
[VS Code Extension Host]  ←→  [Sidecar Node.js Server :39291]  ←→  [LLM Backend]
   TypeScript                    CodeGraph                            Ollama / vLLM
   WebView React UI              ShardManager                        Local or Remote
   Commands / Keybindings        AgentOrchestrator
   AttentionOverlay              MultiAgentRunner          ←→  [Edit Genome Collector]
   GutterHeatmap                 ProjectMemoryGraph               SQLite + opt-in sync
                                 SemanticDriftDetector
                                 CausalDebugAgent
                                 CrossRepoIndexer
                                 VectorStore (vectra)
                                 AirGapModeManager
```

### Process 1: Extension Host (TypeScript)
- Registers commands, keybindings, sidebar, gutter decorations
- Hosts React WebView panels: Chat, Tasks, Shards, Memory, Debug, Review
- Communicates with Sidecar via HTTP on localhost:39291
- Renders AttentionHeatmap overlay directly in editor gutter
- Reads/writes files via VS Code API only (never fs directly)

### Process 2: Sidecar Server (Node.js / Express)
- Runs as a child process spawned by the extension on activation
- Owns all heavy logic: indexing, shard assembly, agent orchestration
- Hosts ProjectMemoryGraph (persistent across sessions via SQLite)
- Hosts EditGenomeCollector (telemetry pipeline)
- Hosts MultiAgentRunner (parallel specialist agents)
- Hosts SemanticDriftDetector (tracks embedding drift on git commits)
- Hosts CausalDebugAgent (stack trace → root cause analysis)
- Hosts CrossRepoIndexer (shared index across repositories)
- Exposes REST + SSE API consumed by Extension Host

### Process 3: LLM Backend (pluggable)
- Default: Ollama on localhost:11434
- Remote: vLLM on RunPod (configurable endpoint + API key)
- Interface: OpenAI-compatible /v1/chat/completions endpoint
- All adapters speak the same internal LLMAdapter interface

