## WHAT NOT TO DO

- Do NOT use `langchain` or `llamaindex` — too heavy, too magical
- Do NOT use Python in the sidecar — pure Node.js only
- Do NOT store embeddings in a separate process — vectra runs in-memory in Node
- Do NOT call the LLM from the Extension Host — always go through sidecar
- Do NOT apply diffs automatically — always require user confirmation
- Do NOT index `node_modules`, `.git`, `dist`, `build`, `.next` — ever
- Do NOT use `window.localStorage` in WebView — use VS Code's `context.globalState`
- Do NOT hardcode the model name — always read from VS Code settings
- Do NOT collect genome data without consent — legal and ethical requirement
- Do NOT make any outbound calls when airgap.enabled = true — throw immediately
- Do NOT run more than 4 parallel LLM calls — hardware constraint
- Do NOT store genome data with identifiable file paths or variable names

