## DEMO SCRIPT v2 (for investor/acquisition presentation)

**Act 1: The Core Innovation (2 min)**
1. Open a 60-file Node.js project
2. Show status bar: "$(shield) NeuroCode | qwen2.5-coder:7b | 67 files | 3.2GB VRAM"
3. Cursor on `createUser()`. Press Ctrl+Shift+A
4. Type: "Add email uniqueness validation before inserting"
5. Watch Attention Heatmap light up in the gutter — blue lines = what the AI read
6. Show Shard Visualizer: 4 files, 2840/3500 tokens, each with reason badge
7. Streamed response appears → View Diff → Accept

**Act 2: The Moat Features (3 min)**
8. Press Ctrl+Shift+R (Review). Four agent cards appear simultaneously
9. Security Agent: flags "SQL injection possible in line 34" with red badge
10. Performance Agent: "Missing database index on users.email" with orange badge
11. Show Project Memory panel: "Last time you edited userController, you also changed validators/email.js"
12. Show Drift Alert on sidebar: "authenticateUser semantic meaning drifted 18% since last commit"
13. Paste a stack trace into Debug panel → Causal Chain appears → root cause highlighted red

**Act 3: The Data Moat (1 min)**
14. Open Genome Stats: "4,231 accepted edits | 89% accept rate | 0 identifiable records"
15. "Every one of these is a training signal no LLM lab can buy. We own this data."

